AttributeList.Text: This function block handles all the logic for handling analog signals and alarms.

This network is used to scale the Analog Input Signal.
The logic checks that the ScaledValueMax is above the Minimum, And that the RawValueMax is above the Min. To avoid an error that could fault the PLC and stop it from running.
If the Input Type = 0, the INT is converted into a real and moved to the ScaledInputValue. If the Input Type = 10 and the ScalingInvalid = FALSE, then the value goes through the scaling process, and is moved into the ScaledInputValue.

This network is used to simulate the analog signal for testing purposes.
If the SimulationMode and GlobalSimulation = FALSE, then the ScaledValue is moved into the PVValue.
If either the SimulationMode or the GlobalSimulation = TRUE, then the scan that this is true, the ScaledInputValue is moved into the SimulationValue. The SimulationValue is then moved into the PVValue. The SimulationValue is adjusted from the HMI to Simulate a Value.

This network monitors the Input value for the HHAlarm.
If PVValue is above the Limit, and the AlarmDisabled = FALSE, and the Qualifier = TRUE, then the DelayTimer begins timing. OR If AlarmActive = TRUE, and the PVValue is still greater then the Limit minus the deadband, the DelayTimer begins timing. OR If the ExternalAlarm = TRUE, the DelayTimer begins timing.
When the DelayTimer.Q (Output) = TRUE, then the AlarmActive is set to TRUE. If the AlarmLatchEnabled = TRUE, then AlarmLatch is also set to TRUE.
High High Analog Alarm - Monitoring for Alarm Condition
